label.value: glial cell-derived neurotrophic factor production

value.value: The regulated release of glial cell line-derived neurotrophic factor from a cell. Glial cell-derived neurotrophic factor (GDNF) is a small protein that potently promotes the survival of many types of neurons, notably dopaminergic and motor neurons.

label.value: envenomation resulting in modulation of blood coagulation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the modulation of the frequency, rate or extent of blood coagulation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in positive regulation of blood coagulation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant activation, maintenance or an increase in the frequency, rate or extent of blood coagulation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of blood coagulation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction in the frequency, rate or extent of blood coagulation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in pore formation in membrane of another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a pore complex in a membrane of the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in modulation of calcium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with a resultant change in the activity of a calcium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of calcium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of a calcium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of voltage-gated calcium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of a voltage-gated calcium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of high voltage-gated calcium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of a high voltage-gated calcium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of low voltage-gated calcium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of a low voltage-gated calcium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of platelet aggregation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction in the frequency, rate or extent of platelet aggregation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in positive regulation of platelet aggregation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant activation, maintenance or an increase in the frequency, rate or extent of platelet aggregation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in modulation of mast cell degranulation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant modulation of blood mast cell degranulation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in positive regulation of mast cell degranulation in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant positive regulation of blood mast cell degranulation in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in blood vessel extracellular matrix damage, causing hemorrhagic damage in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism which causes damage to the extracellular matrix of the blood vessels of the bitten organism, ultimately resulting in hemorrhage in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in impairment of hemostasis in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the inhibition of the process of hemostasis - the stopping of bleeding or the arrest of the circulation to an organ or part - in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in fibrinolysis in another organism

value.value: The process which begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with fibrinolysis, a process that solubilizes fibrin, chiefly by the proteolytic action of plasmin, in the bloodstream of the bitten/stung organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in fibrinogenolysis in another organism

value.value: The process which begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with fibrinogenolysis, a process that degrades fibrinogen at a variety of Arg-Lys bonds, thus impairing fibrinogen clotting in the bloodstream of the bitten/stung organism.

label.value: modulation of transmission of nerve impulse in another organism

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change in the transmission of a nerve impulse in another organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in modulation of transmission of nerve impulse in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant modulation of the transmission of nerve impulses in the bitten organism.

label.value: modulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in another organism

value.value: Any process in which an organism effects a change in the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in another organism.

label.value: negative regulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in another organism

value.value: Any process in which an organism stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in another organism.

label.value: positive regulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in another organism

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in another organism.

label.value: positive regulation of molecular function in another organism

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the function of proteins in a second organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in modulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with a resultant change in the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in positive regulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant activation or increase in the activity of the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in the bitten organism.

label.value: modulation of blood pressure in another organism

value.value: A process by which one organism modulates the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system of another organism.

label.value: negative regulation of blood pressure in another organism

value.value: A process by which one organism decreases the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system of another organism.

label.value: positive regulation of blood pressure in another organism

value.value: A process by which one organism increases the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system of another organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in modulation of blood pressure in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant modulation of the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system of the bitten/stung organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in positive regulation of blood pressure in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant increase of the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system of the bitten/stung organism.

label.value: envenomation resulting in negative regulation of blood pressure in another organism

value.value: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant decrease of the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system of the bitten/stung organism.

label.value: perturbation of signal transduction in another organism

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change in a signal transduction process - a cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell - in a second organism.

label.value: modulation of G protein-coupled receptor activity in another organism

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change in the activity of a G protein-coupled receptor in a second organism.

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change in the activity of a receptor in a second organism.

label.value: positive regulation of G protein-coupled receptor activity in another organism

value.value: A process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a G protein-coupled receptor in a second organism.

label.value: modulation of glucagon-like peptide receptor 1 activity in another organism

label.value: positive regulation of receptor activity in another organism

label.value: glucagon-like peptide 1 receptor activity
